    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix CLAC test command mask initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe CLAC test command handler in the NAS UE AT command parser was not properly initializing the mask field of the at_command_t structure. This led to uninitialized memory being used downstream in command processing, causing inconsistent behavior when handling AT+CLAC=? commands.\n\nThe issue manifested as sporadic failures in AT command processing, particularly when switching between different command types rapidly. In some cases, this would lead to incorrect command routing or unexpected error responses.\n\nRoot cause was the parse_clac_test function not setting at_command->mask, while other similar functions were inconsistently handling this field. This fix ensures the mask is properly initialized to AT_COMMAND_CLAC_MASK (AT_COMMAND_NO_PARAM) for CLAC test commands.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/API/USER/at_command.c`: Added mask initialization in parse_clac_test function to match action command behavior and prevent uninitialized memory access.\n"
}